WEBVTT

00:00:11.310 --> 00:00:13.200
Good afternoon, everybody.

00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:15.940
My name is Jeff Watkins,
and I'm an iOS engineer

00:00:15.940 --> 00:00:18.040
on the Game Center team.

00:00:18.220 --> 00:00:20.940
And today, I have the pleasure of talking
to you about some of the

00:00:21.030 --> 00:00:23.640
new features in GameCenter.

00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:27.310
Now, as you would expect,
there are a lot of things

00:00:27.420 --> 00:00:29.900
under the covers that are new.

00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:34.200
We've accelerated authentication,
so now your players can get

00:00:34.290 --> 00:00:36.320
into the game a lot faster.

00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:40.740
We've also accelerated things like
submitting scores and achievements,

00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:43.900
so they take fewer system resources.

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:46.630
But really, that's the sort of thing that
you've just come to expect from

00:00:46.630 --> 00:00:48.660
us with each rep of the software.

00:00:51.370 --> 00:00:54.200
So they don't merit any more talking.

00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:58.820
But we've talked to you guys a
lot over the last year or so.

00:00:58.820 --> 00:01:04.490
And whether you're a veteran of the
game industry and you've been making

00:01:04.490 --> 00:01:09.800
games since I was actually good at them,
like back in Dig Dug days,

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:13.490
or you're brand new to
building games for iOS,

00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:16.230
you all have one thing in common.

00:01:16.230 --> 00:01:18.620
You're the reason I can't get
my iPad back for my daughter.

00:01:19.750 --> 00:01:24.160
And it's really quite fantastic
what you guys are doing with games.

00:01:24.160 --> 00:01:25.820
They're really, really amazing.

00:01:26.050 --> 00:01:30.080
The sorts of things that you
guys are doing on these little

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:32.440
devices is just incredible.

00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:36.500
It's the sort of thing that you'd
have to take a workstation from

00:01:36.910 --> 00:01:40.820
five years ago to have done,
and now it's on a little phone.

00:01:40.820 --> 00:01:42.190
It's really amazing.

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:47.960
And the fact is,
these are really fun games.

00:01:47.960 --> 00:01:51.820
And you're looking for something to set
your games apart from all the others.

00:01:51.890 --> 00:01:54.410
You're looking for an edge.

00:01:55.420 --> 00:02:00.450
You're looking for something that's
going to make your game a success.

00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:03.090
But I hope you're looking
for something more than that.

00:02:03.330 --> 00:02:07.040
You're looking for something to
make your game a huge success.

00:02:07.910 --> 00:02:11.990
Now, there are a lot of factors that
go into making a game successful.

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:16.550
You've probably heard lots of things
about successful applications all

00:02:16.560 --> 00:02:18.960
throughout the conference so far.

00:02:19.070 --> 00:02:25.250
But there really are three
specific things that we want to

00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:30.830
talk about in terms of games that
we think are really critical to

00:02:30.830 --> 00:02:30.830
the success of all of your games.

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:34.530
The first of those is discoverable.

00:02:34.530 --> 00:02:37.460
Your game has to be discoverable.

00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:40.400
And by that,
I mean people have to find it, right?

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:43.260
If they don't find the game,
they're not going to download it.

00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:48.400
If they don't download it,
they won't play it.

00:02:48.420 --> 00:02:51.460
If they don't play it,
they won't have fun,

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:51.460
they won't tell their friends,
and more people won't

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:51.460
experience your game.

00:02:52.300 --> 00:02:55.020
Second, your game has to be polished.

00:02:55.020 --> 00:03:01.660
And this goes way beyond 3D graphics and
fancy sprites and immersive 3D sound.

00:03:01.780 --> 00:03:06.650
There's a basic level of functionality
that all players expect now,

00:03:06.650 --> 00:03:09.300
and your game has to support that.

00:03:09.300 --> 00:03:14.180
And finally, your game has to be fun.

00:03:14.180 --> 00:03:14.180
If it's not fun,

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:15.790
That's all over.

00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:17.960
You're going to have to go back to
the financial industry and write

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:20.710
stock trading software and cry
yourself to sleep every night.

00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:24.660
So those are the three things
we're going to talk about today.

00:03:24.660 --> 00:03:27.320
Now let's dive right in with number one.

00:03:29.680 --> 00:03:30.600
Discoverable.

00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:33.520
So what do I mean by discoverable?

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:37.040
If you think about how
you learn about games,

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:39.300
you learn about games from your friends.

00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:42.420
And we think that one of the
best places to learn about

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:44.440
games is through Game Center.

00:03:45.530 --> 00:03:49.020
Game Center is fantastic for games.

00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:52.250
You wouldn't expect me to say that
since I am a Game Center engineer.

00:03:52.370 --> 00:03:55.170
But the fact is Game Center is terrific.

00:03:55.250 --> 00:03:58.040
We've got 130 million players.

00:03:58.200 --> 00:04:04.720
Now, those people aren't just signing
up for the latest social networking

00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:04.720
craze and then doing nothing.

00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:07.860
They're out there, they're playing games,
they're having a

00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:09.440
tremendous amount of fun.

00:04:09.440 --> 00:04:14.830
In fact, they're playing so many games
that they're submitting 5

00:04:14.910 --> 00:04:17.280
billion scores every week.

00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:19.640
That's a mind-blowing number.

00:04:19.730 --> 00:04:25.160
It's actually amazing to me, frankly,
that these folks get anything

00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:30.020
done because they're having so
much fun playing your games.

00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:32.630
In fact, we all play your games a
little bit too much too.

00:04:32.920 --> 00:04:37.910
So, 5 billion scores,
130 million players.

00:04:38.180 --> 00:04:44.720
Of the top 100 games,
67 of them are Game Center games.

00:04:44.830 --> 00:04:48.500
And we find that Game Center games
cluster near the top.

00:04:48.620 --> 00:04:52.080
So Game Center games are
typically rated higher and are

00:04:52.080 --> 00:04:54.610
downloaded more than other games.

00:04:54.780 --> 00:04:56.660
So those of you who have
games in Game Center,

00:04:56.890 --> 00:04:58.540
you know exactly what I'm talking about.

00:04:58.690 --> 00:05:00.740
This is a fantastic party.

00:05:00.880 --> 00:05:02.200
Folks are out there,
they're playing games,

00:05:02.200 --> 00:05:03.260
they're having a lot of fun.

00:05:03.260 --> 00:05:05.900
Those of you who don't have
games in Game Center yet,

00:05:05.900 --> 00:05:07.740
dude, what are you waiting for?

00:05:07.740 --> 00:05:11.210
This is the thing you've
got to take advantage of.

00:05:11.410 --> 00:05:14.740
So how does a party get started?

00:05:14.740 --> 00:05:19.020
Well, it all gets started with
game recommendations.

00:05:19.250 --> 00:05:21.850
You want to have some
games on your device.

00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:26.350
And the best way to get games, we find,
is to recommend games that

00:05:26.350 --> 00:05:27.570
you already like playing.

00:05:27.620 --> 00:05:30.710
So, for example,
later we're going to talk about Aideen,

00:05:30.710 --> 00:05:33.820
and she's a racing fan,
she has stock car racing games,

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:36.460
sailboat racing games,
and now she's branching

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:38.320
out to space racing games.

00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:41.860
So naturally,
if there's a new racing game out there,

00:05:41.860 --> 00:05:44.570
we're going to recommend
the racing game to Aideen.

00:05:44.830 --> 00:05:49.880
But also, we'll recommend games to Aideen
based on the games her friends play.

00:05:49.880 --> 00:05:53.470
So her friend Bill loves Railroad Empire,
so naturally you're going to

00:05:53.480 --> 00:05:56.810
recommend that game as well,
because it only makes sense that

00:05:56.810 --> 00:06:00.970
the games that your friends play,
you might want to play with them.

00:06:01.730 --> 00:06:06.040
Now, friends, pretty important deal,
especially if they're going to

00:06:06.040 --> 00:06:08.320
get game recommendations for you.

00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:12.800
So friend recommendations are also
an integral part of Game Center.

00:06:12.890 --> 00:06:16.040
Now, we'll recommend friends
by the games you play.

00:06:16.200 --> 00:06:25.590
So to Aideen, we'll recommend players
that also like racing games.

00:06:25.590 --> 00:06:25.590
But we can also now, in iOS 6,

00:06:25.830 --> 00:06:29.640
We can recommend friends based
on your Facebook profile.

00:06:29.650 --> 00:06:33.900
So you can link your Game Center account
with your Facebook account,

00:06:34.020 --> 00:06:37.540
and right away you can find all
of your friends from Facebook,

00:06:37.670 --> 00:06:40.330
you can find their Game Center profiles.

00:06:40.420 --> 00:06:45.790
And we think this is a great way
to get players' friend graphs

00:06:45.790 --> 00:06:45.790
up and running very quickly.

00:06:47.220 --> 00:06:51.620
Now, friends are really important.

00:06:51.620 --> 00:06:55.630
Every afternoon special you've ever
seen drums that into your head.

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:57.540
Friends are your lifeline.

00:06:57.540 --> 00:06:58.820
They do everything for you.

00:06:58.820 --> 00:07:04.190
If you think about how you and your
friends interact regarding games,

00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:07.340
you can see why friends are so important.

00:07:07.340 --> 00:07:10.100
When my team and I are
hanging out playing games,

00:07:10.100 --> 00:07:11.840
we don't just play the game.

00:07:11.980 --> 00:07:13.680
We talk about the games we have played.

00:07:13.680 --> 00:07:17.270
In fact, most of the games that I enjoy
playing with my family,

00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:20.540
I discovered because of my friends.

00:07:20.540 --> 00:07:25.490
And so friends are crucial to
the discoverability of your game.

00:07:25.750 --> 00:07:29.050
So friends tell friends about games.

00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:30.980
It's that simple, right?

00:07:30.980 --> 00:07:34.570
Baked into Game Center from day one
has been the ability to tell your

00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:37.340
friends about the games you're playing.

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:42.040
All you have to do is
tap that little button,

00:07:42.040 --> 00:07:45.340
up comes an email sheet,
you address it to some of

00:07:45.340 --> 00:07:45.340
your friends and whoosh,
now they know.

00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:47.690
That's a good start.

00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:52.560
And in iOS 5, we added in-app rating.

00:07:52.670 --> 00:07:56.370
So previously,
you had to ask players to pop off

00:07:56.460 --> 00:08:00.150
to the app store and rate your
game and maybe write a review.

00:08:00.150 --> 00:08:03.950
But now, right after they finish playing
and they've had a great time,

00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:08.080
they bring up their leaderboard to see
how they compare against their friends,

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:12.090
and right there they can rate your
game and let everybody in the app store

00:08:12.090 --> 00:08:14.360
know what a great game you've built.

00:08:14.360 --> 00:08:18.730
Now, this is pretty critical, right,
because you can imagine we recommend

00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:24.090
games that are five stars before we'll
recommend games that are one star.

00:08:24.580 --> 00:08:26.260
Now, we can't hide it.

00:08:26.310 --> 00:08:30.020
Up there in the top right-hand corner
is a brand-new feature in iOS 6,

00:08:30.020 --> 00:08:31.440
the Facebook Like button.

00:08:31.440 --> 00:08:35.000
Now,
if your players have Facebook accounts,

00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:38.370
they can tap on the Like button,
and that will send a

00:08:38.380 --> 00:08:41.990
message off to Facebook,
and in their friends' news feeds,

00:08:41.990 --> 00:08:45.980
they'll see the fact
that you like this game.

00:08:46.480 --> 00:08:49.910
Now, when their friends tap on the link,
we'll take them directly

00:08:49.910 --> 00:08:52.720
to the App Store,
and they can download your game.

00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:56.710
We think this is a fantastic way
for your players to spread the word

00:08:56.710 --> 00:08:59.170
about what a great game you've built.

00:09:01.670 --> 00:09:05.280
Now, your friends,
when you're playing games and

00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:08.800
you're talking about games,
we don't stop at just telling

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:10.990
each other about new games,
do we?

00:09:10.990 --> 00:09:19.960
If your friends are
anything like my friends,

00:09:19.960 --> 00:09:19.960
they kind of, shall we say,
brag about their scores.

00:09:20.290 --> 00:09:25.330
And it makes me feel a little bad
because I'm a terrible game player.

00:09:25.330 --> 00:09:27.430
But we wanted to take advantage of that,
right?

00:09:27.540 --> 00:09:31.220
Because this is the sort of
energy that players already have.

00:09:31.320 --> 00:09:33.540
They're already doing this activity.

00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:38.660
So let's give them the facility to
do that right inside Game Center.

00:09:38.830 --> 00:09:43.770
So here you'll see the brand-new
score and achievement detail.

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:46.730
And right there is the share button.

00:09:46.730 --> 00:09:49.570
All your players have
to do is tap on that.

00:09:51.520 --> 00:09:55.930
and they'll get the system-wide
UI activity view controller.

00:09:56.050 --> 00:09:57.790
And from there,
they can share their scores

00:09:57.790 --> 00:10:04.520
and achievements via email,
via iMessage, via Twitter or Facebook.

00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:07.580
In this case,
I'm going to tap on Facebook.

00:10:07.720 --> 00:10:10.890
Up comes the system
composed sheet for Facebook.

00:10:11.010 --> 00:10:13.830
We've prepopulated that with
information about the game they're

00:10:13.830 --> 00:10:17.920
playing and a link to Game Center.

00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:22.770
When the player taps post,
all of his friends' devices will

00:10:22.780 --> 00:10:28.080
see the update to their Facebook or
Twitter or any other social network

00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:33.350
stream with the information about
the liked and the shared score.

00:10:33.450 --> 00:10:35.580
So that's great, right?

00:10:35.580 --> 00:10:38.210
We could bring them to the App Store,
but that's not really

00:10:38.210 --> 00:10:39.340
how we wanted to do this.

00:10:39.340 --> 00:10:42.340
So when they tap on that link,
we'll actually bring them into

00:10:42.340 --> 00:10:45.610
Game Center and we'll show them
the achievement or the score

00:10:45.950 --> 00:10:47.840
that the player has shared.

00:10:47.870 --> 00:10:47.900
And when they tap on that link,
we'll actually bring them

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:50.060
into Game Center and right
there from inside Game Center,

00:10:50.060 --> 00:10:53.680
if they don't already have the game,
they can download the game.

00:10:53.690 --> 00:10:57.280
Plus, if they're not already
friends via Game Center,

00:10:57.300 --> 00:11:00.190
there'll be a button there to
send a friend request so that now

00:11:00.190 --> 00:11:04.180
they'll have found another friend
via their social networking.

00:11:04.180 --> 00:11:06.600
So shared scores and
achievements are great,

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:09.030
and that's part of the equation.

00:11:09.270 --> 00:11:13.340
But my friends don't stop at
sharing their scores with me,

00:11:13.540 --> 00:11:15.280
much as I wish they would.

00:11:15.390 --> 00:11:18.590
They also go on to challenge me
to try and beat their scores.

00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:22.200
And so we've built that
right into Game Center.

00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:24.090
Challenges are gonna be huge.

00:11:24.370 --> 00:11:28.150
Now, the important thing that you're
probably asking yourself is,

00:11:28.150 --> 00:11:32.240
jeez, how much code do I have to write
to take advantage of challenges?

00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:33.300
I won't kid you.

00:11:33.300 --> 00:11:36.140
You can write code to take
advantage of challenges,

00:11:36.140 --> 00:11:37.520
but you don't have to.

00:11:37.520 --> 00:11:41.930
Out of the box in iOS 6,
every game that supports scores and

00:11:42.130 --> 00:11:45.240
achievements supports challenges.

00:11:45.240 --> 00:11:47.160
Now this is gonna be big.

00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:52.240
As you saw this morning, Jetpack Joyride,
they did a great job of integrating

00:11:52.620 --> 00:11:54.740
challenges in just a few days.

00:11:54.740 --> 00:12:01.290
And we think it adds a much richer
degree of immersion to the game.

00:12:01.500 --> 00:12:05.550
So the way this works is we tap
on the challenge friends button

00:12:05.550 --> 00:12:07.960
and up comes the friend picker.

00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:09.950
Right there,
I can pick some of my friends

00:12:09.950 --> 00:12:11.360
to send the challenge to.

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:13.960
And I want to call your
attention to something.

00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:17.330
You'll see that we've broken
this off into two parts.

00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:21.700
We have the friends who play the game,
of course, but we also have friends

00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:23.180
who don't play the game.

00:12:23.180 --> 00:12:24.750
And that's actually critical.

00:12:24.860 --> 00:12:28.190
Because you can send challenges to
friends who don't play the game.

00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:30.880
And when they get the
challenge notification,

00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:33.540
they can tap on the banner or bring
it up in the notification center and

00:12:33.580 --> 00:12:35.780
they'll get taken right to the app store.

00:12:35.930 --> 00:12:38.740
They can download the game and then bam,
they can start playing

00:12:38.740 --> 00:12:39.810
and beat the challenge.

00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:45.820
So once I've picked my friends,
then I get a chance to send

00:12:45.820 --> 00:12:46.950
a little personal message.

00:12:47.150 --> 00:12:49.800
In my case, it's almost always snarky.

00:12:49.990 --> 00:12:52.750
But I click send or tap send.

00:12:54.600 --> 00:12:55.570
And off it goes.

00:12:55.700 --> 00:13:01.600
The push notification goes to my friends,
and they get the banner that comes down.

00:13:02.920 --> 00:13:05.850
And lo and behold,
they get an opportunity to jump

00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:08.240
inside the game and start playing.

00:13:08.240 --> 00:13:12.880
So challenges are really a big deal
because they take a single-player game

00:13:13.020 --> 00:13:17.880
and they raise it up to the level of
a multiplayer game because it brings

00:13:17.880 --> 00:13:20.380
their friends into the equation.

00:13:20.380 --> 00:13:23.400
We think it's going to be a
great feature for your games.

00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:26.820
Now, multiplayer is a big deal, as well,
right?

00:13:26.840 --> 00:13:30.820
People like playing
games with other people.

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:34.550
And that's why we all get
together around a board game and

00:13:34.640 --> 00:13:36.960
spend far too much time there.

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:41.580
And multiplayer invitations are
also a critical aspect to the

00:13:42.040 --> 00:13:44.730
discoverability of your game,
right?

00:13:44.810 --> 00:13:47.980
Because if you think about it,
one of the things that happens

00:13:47.980 --> 00:13:51.020
a lot is someone will say,
hey, let's go play this game.

00:13:51.020 --> 00:13:54.320
Right there, you don't have the game,
but you're going to go play

00:13:54.320 --> 00:13:55.970
and you're going to have fun.

00:13:55.970 --> 00:13:59.910
So, Aideen, as I said,
she's a big racing game fan and

00:13:59.910 --> 00:14:05.840
she wants to play the latest space
pylon game with her buddies Bill,

00:14:05.840 --> 00:14:06.850
Claire,

00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:11.600
sets everything up,
brings up the matchmaking interface,

00:14:11.840 --> 00:14:13.700
sends out the invitations.

00:14:13.720 --> 00:14:14.960
Bill gets the invitation.

00:14:15.190 --> 00:14:17.100
Claire and Deirdre get the invitation.

00:14:17.180 --> 00:14:18.500
But they're not big gamers.

00:14:18.740 --> 00:14:24.580
So from the invitation,
we take them to the app store where

00:14:24.580 --> 00:14:28.040
they can download Space Pylon.

00:14:28.040 --> 00:14:28.170
And the moment they download it,
they get brought into the

00:14:28.170 --> 00:14:28.170
game and they're ready to go.

00:14:28.590 --> 00:14:32.070
So, as happens very frequently
in cases like this,

00:14:32.150 --> 00:14:35.200
Claire knocks their socks off.

